		<pb n="1"/>
			<p rend="align(center)"><placeName>Easton Pa.</placeName> <date>April 23. 1851</date>.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">The new congregation which of late <del>arose</del><lb/> <hi rend="underline">was</hi> started in this place under the name of &#44;&#44;Emanu El&#34;<lb/> will to all appearance be of but very short duration&#44;<lb/> since the same causes which effected the split of the<lb/> old and gave rise to this new congregation begin to prevail in<lb/> much higher degree in the latter. Not the spirit of true<lb/> religion&#44; that of love&#44; <sic>piece</sic> and righteousness is there<lb/> to be found&#44; but in the contrary nothing but tyranny<lb/> injustice and irony is doing and therefore continual guards<lb/> and lamentable scandals are taking place. The conse&#45;<lb/>quence of all this is&#44; that this congregation cannot<lb/> get a suitable man to act as minister&#44; three persons already <del>were</del><lb/> soho<add>&#63;</add> had been solicited to come here and occupy this<lb/> place have declined on hearing what here is going<lb/> on&#44; so that they were obliged to write for one to <placeName>Ger&#45;<lb/>many</placeName> but&#8212;in vain. What characterizes this congregation<lb/> and throws to me light over their religious principles<lb/> is the fact that their principal leader and present<lb/> minister <del>of</del> is a man who acknowledges no religion<lb/> at all <del>and</del>&#59; after having performed the service in the syna&#45;<lb/>gogue he returns <del>to me</del> to <del>go</del> his <del>grocery store</del> business and violates<lb/> the sacred law of the <date>sabbath</date> for which he just now<lb/> had praised God &#44;&#44;who has given it to us&#34; thus evidently<lb/> showing that he has only his play with religion.</p>
			<p>That our holy religion is thus profaned in the eyes of our<lb/> <sic>christian</sic> brethern is much to be lamented and the sooner</p>
		<pb n="2"/>
			<p>a congregation of this kind would cease to be the better</p>
          <p rend="indent(7)">A&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Veritas</p>
			<p><persname>Mr. Editor&#33;</persname></p>
			<p>I request you to give these few lines a space in your<lb/> much esteemed paper <del>by</del> whereby you will oblige <del>your</del></p>
          <p rend="indent(5)">yours truly</p>
          <p rend="indent(5)"><persName role="author">L M Cohen</persName></p>
			<p>P. S. Please send me a copy of the next number<lb/> of your paper.</p>
		<pb n="3"/>
			<p><addressee>Rev. Mr. Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p>Editor of the Occident</p>
